      "content": "that makes sense. but i was a bit confused by the \"primitive\" part u mentioned earlier. usually, when people talk about those \"older\" or \"primitive\" groups, they're talking about indigenous tribes or people in developing parts of the world. does that mean those cultures are basically just stuck in an earlier stage of development compared to us? like, are they closer to the starting point of that \"evolution\" process?",
